Here is a clear, highly structured prompt you can copy and paste directly to the other AI. It explicitly lays out the logic, the priority rules, and the exact UI changes you want, ensuring it doesn't break the IndexedDB or Cache features we just set up.
**Copy and paste the text below to the other AI:**
> I have a single-file HTML/JS anime schedule board. It currently fetches a user's AniList "Watching" list and a SubsPlease RSS feed to calculate release slots.
> I want to add a secondary, fallback RSS feed using a Nyaa link wrapped in an rss2json proxy.
> Here is the new URL to add: https://api.rss2json.com/v1/api.json?rss_url=https%3A%2F%2Fnyaa.si%2F%3Fpage%3Drss%26u%3Dvaryg1001
> Please update my code to implement this new feed with the following strict rules:
> **1. Strict Hierarchy & Priority (SubsPlease is King)**
> SubsPlease is my primary source. The Nyaa feed must act *strictly* as a fallback. When matching shows, if a show exists in the SubsPlease data, the code must completely ignore the Nyaa data for that show. Nyaa should never overwrite or take a slot that SubsPlease can fill.
> **2. Gap-Filling Logic**
> Nyaa should only provide a release slot if SubsPlease has not found the show yet. However, if a show is initially populated by Nyaa, but later SubsPlease picks it up, the SubsPlease data must immediately take over and overwrite the Nyaa data on the next load.
> **3. JSON to XML Conversion**
> Because rss2json returns JSON but my parser (parseGenericFeed) expects XML, you must process the fetch result by mapping the JSON items into a dummy XML string <rss><channel><item>...</item></channel></rss>. Please ensure the pubDate space is replaced with a T and appended with a Z to maintain strict UTC formatting before passing it to parseGenericFeed.
> **4. UI & Health Status Integration**
>  * **Stats Overview:** Update the renderSummary function and HTML to include a new stat card specifically for "Nyaa RSS" (showing how many shows are currently using Nyaa slots) alongside the existing "SubsPlease RSS" card.
>  * **Health Footer:** The fetch request for the Nyaa URL must be wrapped in the Promise.allSettled block. If it fails, it must push an error to the state.notes array so the footer shows an "Unhealthy" status and logs the error, exactly how SubsPlease does.
>  * **Board Chips:** Please ensure that if a show is using a Nyaa slot, the UI chip reflects this (e.g., <span class="chip nyaa">NYAA</span> instead of the RSS/AniList chip) so I can visually see which fallback was used.
> Please provide the complete, updated HTML file. Do not remove or break my existing Code. Here is my current code:
> [INSERT YOUR HTML CODE HERE]
> 
That prompt locks the AI into your exact architecture so it won't try to rewrite the whole app, and it makes the "SubsPlease > Nyaa" hierarchy an absolute rule!
